post_text:
08/07/2020

Parents,

Due to a possible Covid 19 positive exposure in our Child Nutrition Department, the Marshall County Health Department has advised our administration to close our cafeteria. We will be unable to provide meals to our students, therefore our district will be switching to Distant Learning starting Monday, August 10, 2020.

Parents of elementary students will be contacted by their child’s teacher. Middle and High School students will have distance learning packets available for pickup on Tuesday, August 11, 2020 from 9am to 3pm. The pickup location for Middle and High School packets will be between the Middle and High School Buildings.

We are in the process of preparing our Chromebooks with the necessary software needed for virtual learning. More information will be provided when it is available.

Brian Brister
Superintendent of Schools

Kingston Elementary Enrollment

Tuesday, July 14th-Thursday, July 16th
8:00 am to 2:00 pm

1 person per family will be allowed to come to door to pick up enrollment packet or one can be brought out to you. Packets will not be filled out at the school! Packets will need to be returned in the school in same manner.

This enrollment is for all returning students and NEW students PreK-5th Grade. All students must complete a new enrollment packet for the 2020-2021 school year and provide a current residence verification.

For NEW STUDENTS-Parents MUST provide: Valid ID, Childs Certified Birth Certificate, Proof of Residence, Childs Shot Record, Social Security Card, CDIB Card, or Tribal Letter.

Kingston Public School Parents/Guardians in need of obtaining their child’s medication during our extended time out of school please see the below information in regards to picking up those medications.

Pick Up Dates/Times:

Friday, March 20, 2020 from 8:00 am – 9:00 am

Monday, March 23, 2020 from 11:30 am – 12:30 pm

Pickup Location:

Kingston Elementary School, North Marshall Street parking lot.

This is the ‘elementary after school pick up line area’, on the East side of the elementary school.

Pickup Procedure:

Medications will be picked up ‘drive through’ style to help maintain social distancing guidelines set by the Center for Disease Control.

(This ‘drive through’ style is the same procedure we currently use for elementary school student afternoon pickups).

Proper Identification:

Please be prepared to have identification and sign a receipt for picking up the medication.



The dates/times/location apply to all students with medications regardless of campus in attendance.

14 TEXOMA STUDENTS WILL WIN A $1000 SCHOLARSHIP

We are excited to announce the Texoma Chevy Dealers Student Scholarship Program! Your 2020 high school’s seniors are invited to submit a 2 to 3 minute video for a chance to be one of the 14 that will win a $1000 SCHOLARSHIP that can help pay for college or trade school.

The application and video submission website
http://texomachevydealersscholarships.com/ gives details for video content requirements and an easy way to submit their application and video online.

Dates to Remember:
• Submission dates: 2/4/20 to 2/29/20
• Winner selection period: 3/1/20 to 3/15/20
• Winners announced late March through April
